0was%20entirely%20surprised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pros%20of%20dating%20someone%20you%20already%20live%20with%20are%20plenty%3A%20an%20easy%2C%2010-second%20commute%20across%20the%20living%20room%20to%20see%20them%2C%20skipping%20the%20awkward%20beginning%20stages%20of%20dating%20because%20you've%20already%20seen%20each%20other%20unfiltered%2C%20and%20having%20a%20strong%20friendship%20as%20the%20base%20of%20your%20romantic%20relationship.%20And%2C%20unlike%20many%20couples%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-in-with-partner-for-the-first-time-tips-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20move%20in%20together%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20dating%20for%20a%20while%2C%20we%20didn't%20have%20to%20go%20through%20a%20roommate%20adjustment%20phase.%20We%20met%20each%20other%20the%20day%20we%20moved%20into%20the%20loft%2C%20so%20for%20the%20full%20time%20we've%20known%20each%20other%2C%20we've%20never%20not%20lived%20together.%20Living%20together%20is%20fully%20baked%20into%20our%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20because%20of%20this%2C%20when%20we%20decided%20to%20move%20out%20of%20the%20loft%20and%20get%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarried-couple-doesnt-live-together-anymore-it-improved-relationship-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eour%20own%20apartment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20just%20us%20two%2C%20we%20knew%20we%20needed%20to%20maintain%20having%20our%20own%20rooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHaving%20separate%20bedrooms%20was%20what%20we%20were%20used%20to%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20visited%20one%20one-bedroom%20apartment%20just%20to%20check%20it%20out%20and%20knew%20immediately%20it%20wasn't%20for%20us.%20Logistically%2C%20one-bedroom%20apartments%20are%20so%20much%20smaller.%20Sure%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdink-lifestyle-nyc-apartment-photos-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eour%20combined%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20could%20get%20a%20very%2