ons%20could%20pick%20better%20targets%20to%20put%20the%20squeeze%20on%20Russia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWestern%20nations'%20attempts%20at%20ending%20Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20via%20economic%20sanctions%20are%20hitting%20a%20snag%2C%20and%20the%20measures%20seem%20not%20as%20large%20a%20hit%20to%20Vladimir%20Putin%20as%20expected.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESanctions%20and%20trade%20restrictions%20have%20slammed%20Russia's%20economy%20since%20it%20invaded%20Ukraine%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20targeting%20key%20areas%20like%20energy%2C%20freezing%20foreign%20assets%2C%20and%20cutting%20the%20nation's%20financial%20ties%20to%20much%20of%20the%20West.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20Russia's%20wartime%20economy%20has%20done%20OK%20despite%20all%20that.%20Following%20a%201.2%25%20GDP%20dip%20in%202022%2C%20Moscow%20boasted%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-resilience-companies-bankruptcy-rise-sharply-amid-sanctions-2024%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOn%252Dthe%252Dground%2520difficulties%2520in%2520Russia%26amp%3Btext%3DIt%2520also%2520stands%2520in%2520contrast%2Chigh%2520interest%2520rates%2520are%2520biting.%5C%22%3E%20a%203.6%25%20annual%20growth%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202023%2C%20hitting%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-worker-shortage-ukraine-war-military-wages-unemployment-2024-1%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAs%2520of%2520December%252C%2520Moscow%2520needed%2Cdata%2520from%2520the%2520Russian%2520government.%5C%22%3Eall-time%20low%20unemployment%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%202.9%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20expert%20Owen%20Matthews%2C%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BOverreach%3A%20The%20Inside%20Story%20of%20Putin%20and%20Russia's%20War%20Against%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20Business%20Insider%20on%20Friday%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnord-stream-pipeline-leaks-were-sabotage-explosives-traces-found-sweden-2022-11%5C%22%3Ethe%20explosion%20of%20the%20Nord%20Stream%20pipelines%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20September%202022%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20bigger%20blow%20to%20Russia's%20economy%20than%20the%20West's%20sanctions%20so%20far.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20said%20the%20sanctions%20toolkit%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bporous%2C%26quot%3B%20giving%20Moscow%20many%20ways%20to%20slip%20through%20the%20web%20of%20restrictions%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20lot%20more%20Western%20countries%20can%20do%20to%20ramp%20up%20the%20pressure.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiam%20Peach%2C%20a%20senior%20emerging%20markets%20economist%20of%20Capital%20Economics%2C%20highlighted%20Russia's%20adeptness%20at%20sidestepping%20trade%20restrictions%20in%20a%20note%20last%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20US%20has%20tightened%20sanctions%20evasion%20on%20firms%20that%20help%20Russia%20import%20through%20third%20countries%2C%20but%20trade%20has%20a%20way%20of%20finding%20new%20routes%20and%20it's%20hard%20to%20police.%20If%20it%20is%20profitable%20to%20evade%20sanctions%2C%20some%20firms%20will%20take%20the%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Peach%2C%20sanctions%20haven't%20halted%20money%20from%20non-Western%20countries%20flowing%20to%20Russia.%20Even%20G7's%20bid%20to%20curb%20export%20income%20through%20a%20%2460%20per%20barrel%20cap%20on%20the%20price%20of%20oil%20hasn't%20really%20hobbled%20Moscow's%20oil%20trade.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22FX%20Share%20of%20Russian%20Export%20Settlement%20(%25)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65eb8a0190413ab8e1db1bea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22355%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFX%20Share%20of%20Russian%20Export%20Settlement%20(%25)%3Cp%3ESource%3A%20Central%20Bank%20of%20Russia%2C%20Capital%20Economics%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20US%20has%20noted%20a%20large%20increase%20in%20banking%20flows%20between%20Russia%20and%20Turkey%20and%20the%20UAE.%20The%20West%20has%20reduced%20imports%20of%20Russian%20energy%20significantly%20but%20Russia%20has%20largely%20re-routed%20oil%20exports%20to%20Asia.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Matthews%20notes%20that%20European%20nations%20rarely%20say%20no%20to%20certain%20energy%20supplies%20from%20Russia%2C%20sabotaging%20their%20own%20attempts%20at%20punishing%20Putin.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20whole%20kind%20of%20dirty%20secret%20behind%20all%20the%20European%20sanctions%20packages%20was%20that%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20Europe%20talked%20a%20big%20game%20about%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%2C%20but%20they%20never%20sanctioned%20Russian%20gas%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20regard%20to%20US-dominated%20financial%20sanctions%2C%20limited%20headway%20has%20been%20made%2C%20according%20to%20Matthews.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dominance%20of%20the%20US%20dollar%20as%20a%20trade%20and%20reserve%20currency%20forced%20Russia%20to%20de-dollarize%2C%20and%20Russia%20can%20still%20bypass%20the%20US-controlled%20global%20finance%20system%20with%20the%20help%20of%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia-China%20Goods%20Trade%20(SA%2C%20%24bn)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65eb89c1ce7f1785b2e83169%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22355%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussia-China%20Goods%20Trade%20(SA%2C%20%24bn)%3Cp%3ESource%3A%20Refinitiv%2C%20Capital%20Economics%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInadvertently%2C%20that%20sort%20of%20sanctions%20regime%20has%20just%20encouraged%20more%20Renminbi%20denominated%20transactions%20and%20has%20massively%20boosted%20Dubai%20specifically%20as%20the%20major%20sort%20of%20non-American%20dominated%20hub%20for%20financial%20transactions%2C%26quot%3B%20Matthews%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20else%20can%20the%20West%20do%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EPeach%20wrote%20that%20the%20West%20could%20squeeze%20Russian%20energy%20more%20by%20slapping%20secondary%20sanctions%20on%20third-party%20purchases%20of%20oil%20and%20gas%20from%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRussia%20doesn't%20need%20to%20borrow%20from%20abroad%2C%20but%20it%20does%20need%20foreign%20currency%20in%20the%20form%20of%20energy%20exports%20to%20finance%20the%20budget%2C%20pay%20for%20imports%2C%20and%20stabilize%20the%20ruble.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20unlikely%20for%20the%20West%20to%20take%20this%20path%2C%20he%20added%2C%20given%20Russia's%20energy%20dominance%20and%20the%20risk%20of%20sparking%20volatility%20that%20could%20end%20up%20antagonizing%20partners%20like%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlternatively%2C%20the%20US%20could%20target%20Russia's%20non-oil%20exports%2C%20particularly%20industrial%20metals%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Frussia-gas-lng-eu-europe-energy-crisis-supplies-western-sanctions-2023-3%5C%22%3Eliquefied%20natural%20gas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Peach%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20current%20sanctions%20falling%20short%2C%20Peach%20estimates%20GDP%20growth%20for%20the%20country%20to%20clock%20in%20at%203.0%25-3.5%25%20this%20year%20and%20year-end%20inflation%20at%205.5%25-6.0%25.%20However%2C%20he%20reaffirmed%20that%20sanctions%20are%20set%20to%20persist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSanctions%20are%20unlikely%20to%20be%20rolled%20back%20over%20the%20next%20six%20years%2C%20especially%20if%20Russia%20mobilizes%20further%20and%20pursues%20a%20more%20aggressive%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20Peach%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20even%20with%20a%20negotiated%20settlement%2C%20unfreezing%20Russia's%20foreign%20exchange%20reserves%20is%20probably%20%26quot%3Bout%20of%20the%20question.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-ukraine-war-western-san