the%20Soft%20Cleanser%20product.%20The%20under%20%2410%20cleaning%20agent%20works%20by%20cutting%20into%20the%20top%20layer%20of%20metal%20and%20removing%20the%20thin%20layer%20with%20the%20rust%20speck%20embedded%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20of%20the%20Cybertruck%20owners%20who%20spoke%20to%20BI%20said%20they%20had%20already%20used%20Barkeepers%20Friend%20on%20their%20vehicles'%20spots%20and%20stains%2C%20crediting%20the%20cleaning%20agent%20with%20taking%20off%20all%20imperfections.%20A%20fourth%20owner%20ordered%20some%20of%20the%20cleaner%20soon%20after%20he%20saw%20the%20Facebook%20groups%20raving%20about%20it%20and%20said%20he%20has%20plans%20to%20use%20it%20down%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Barkeepers%20Friend%20approach%20%E2%80%94%20followed%20up%20by%20a%20quick%20Windex%20wash%20%E2%80%94%20doesn't%20appear%20to%20be%20a%20particularly%20sophisticated%20solution.%20The%20cleaning%20agents%20are%20typically%20reserved%20for%20household%20cleaning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20seen%20a%20ton%20of%20Barkeepers%20Friend%20being%20advertised%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20even%20know%20what%20that%20is%2C%20and%20I%20used%20to%20work%20on%20cars%2C%26quot%3B%20Jay%20Larson%2C%20a%20Cybertruck%20owner%20in%20Arizona%20who%20previously%20detailed%20vehicles%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMore%20drastic%20measures%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20cleaning%20solvents%20may%20be%20a%20quick%20fix%20for%20dirty%20Cybertrucks%2C%20four%20of%20the%20new%20owners%20said%20they%20had%20already%20or%20were%20in%20the%20process%20of%20getting%20their%20vehicles%20wrapped.%20A%20vehicle%20vinyl%20wrap%20covers%20the%20entirety%20of%20a%20car.%20It%20is%20often%20a%20different%20color%20or%20finish%20to%20give%20the%20automobile%20a%20unique%20look%20while%20also%20serving%20as%20a%20protective%20layer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20at%20discounted%20sponsorship%20prices%2C%20such%20wraps%20can%20cost%20upwards%20of%20%245%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20on%20top%20of%20the%20up%20to%20%2499%2C990%20for%20the%20Cybertruck%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20owners%20like%20Larson%20simply%20bought%20the%20wrap%20to%20make%20their%20Cybertrucks%20stand%20out.%20He%20opted%20for%20a%20blue%20matte.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224733%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jay%20Larson%20poses%20with%20his%20new%20Cybertruck%2C%20which%20he%20had%20wrapped.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ea23cb6080194819fdc342%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222367%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJay%20Larson%20poses%20with%20his%20new%20Cybertruck%2C%20which%20he%20had%20wrapped%20in%20a%20blue%20matte.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jay%20Larson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20others%20turned%20to%20wrapping%20as%20a%20preventive%20measure%20against%20the%20spots%20and%20stains%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20minimize%20the%20upkeep%20of%20the%20stainless%20steel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWin%20Cramer%2C%20a%20California-based%20Cybertruck%20owner%20who%20got%20his%20vehicle%20in%20February%2C%20chose%20a%20clear%20PPF%20wrap%20that%20cost%20him%20about%20%245%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20got%20the%20PPF%20filter%20purely%20for%20fingerprints.%20It%20was%20a%20fingerprint%20magnet%20which%20drove%20me%20bananas%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI%20of%20his%20new%20truck.%20%26quot%3BThe%20fingerprints%20certainly%20wash%20off%2C%20and%20I%20used%20Windex%20wipes%2C%20but%20I%20shouldn't%20have%20to%20do%20that.%20That%20kind%20of%20sucks%2C%20so%20the%20wrap%20was%20my%20way%20of%20getting%20around%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20extra%20upkeep%20isn't%20entirely%20unexpected%20for%20experienced%20Tesla%20owners%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20have%20taken%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fev-electric-car-sales-plateau-early-adopters-competition-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erole%20of%20early%20adopters%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20feel%20like%20Tesla%20could%20give%20us%20more%20recommendations%20on%20these%20sorts%20of%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Wang%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20Cybertruck%20upkeep.%20%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20like%20we're%20left%20in%20the%20dark%20and%20have%20to%20blindly%20experiment%20on%20our%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20this%20is%20kind%20of%20standard%20for%20Tesla%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BThey%20let%20others%20figure%20out%20the%20kinks%20as%20they%20go.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-owner%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOther%20owners%3C%2Fa%3E%20pointed%20out%20that%20it's%20not%20uncommon%20for%20higher-end%20vehicles%20to%20require%20a%20little%20extra%20upkeep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20money%20you%20spend%2C%20you%20generally%20take%20care%20of%20it%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20Cramer%2C%20who%20also%20owns%20a%20Porsche%20Taycan%20Turbo%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BSome%20of%20it's%20just%20natural%20with%20the%20investment%20that's%20made.%20The%20Cybertruck%20is%20a%20car%20person's%20car%20at%20this%20stage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Cybertruck%20is%20at%20a%20lower%20price%20point%20than%20most%20luxury%20cars%2C%20but%20it%20certainly%20has%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-cybertruck-new-status-car-celebrities-billionaires-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esame%20clientele%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20might%20not%20be%20the%20case%20for%20long.%20If%20Tesla%20hits%20Musk's%20ambitious%20production%20targets%20for%20the%20Cybertruck%2C%20Tesla%20is%20likely%20to%20face%20less%20forgiving%20buyers%2C%20automotive%20analyst%20Ivan%20Drury%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20have%20a%20rare%20and%20exotic%20car%2C%20people%20are%20willing%20to%20put%20up%20with%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20won't%20be%20true%20if%20it%20becomes%20as%20commonplace%20as%20something%20like%20a%20Camry.%20Regular%20people%20don't%20want%20to%20spend%20that%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20now%2C%20these%20drivers%20say%20the%20truck%20is%20worth%20whatever%20inconveniences%20it%20may%20bring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTesla%20is%20the%20best%20car%20on%20the%20road.%20It's%20the%20best%20car%20to%20drive%2C%26quot%3B%20Green%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20driving%20experience%20is%20just%20excellent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcybertruck-upkeep-barkeepers-friend-tesla-fanatics-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710067022000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65eb691cce7f1785b2e811de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcybertruck-upkeep-barkeepers-friend-tesla-fanatics-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Six%20Tesla%20Cybertruck%20owners%20said%20reports%20of%20rust%20specks%20and%20smudges%20on%20the%20car's%20stainless%20steel%20had%20done%20little%20to%20detract%20from%20their%20enthusiasm.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22esnodgrass%40insider.com%20(Erin%20Snodgrass%2CGrace%20Kay)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcybertruck-upkeep-barkeepers-friend-tesla-fanatics-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22And%20Then%20There%20Will%20Be%20None%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16094246%2Fimage1440x560cropped.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20child%20victim%E2%80%99s%20body%20is%20the%20moral%20Ground%20Zero%20of%20conflict%20and%20the%20global%20silence%20around%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FAfghan_Girl%23%2Fmedia%2FFile%3ASharbat_Gula.jpg%5C%22%3EAfghan%20Girl%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2015)%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ficonicphotos.files.wordpress.com%2F2009%2F08%2Fkevin-carter-vulture.jpg%5C%22%3Evulture%20and%20the%20little%20girl%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2013)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.arabnews.com%2Fnode%2F978831%2F%257B%257B%5C%22%3EAylan%20Kurdi%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2015)%20and%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F03%2F09%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fyazan-kafarneh-gaza-starvation.html%3Funlocked_article_code%3D1.bU0.L7Pa.YczkkiFGRDW2%26smid%3Durl-share%5C%22%3EYazan%20Kafarneh%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2024).%20Media%20photographs%20of%20the%20impact%20of%20armed%20conflict%20on%20children%2C%20arguably%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20in%20any%20condition%20of%20conflict%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmeaning-is-a-physiognomy-or-the-child-victim-as-the-face-of-the-modern-age%5C%22%3Eideal%20victim%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20have%20marched%20endlessly%20through%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20famous%20social%20documentary%20filmmaker%20Jacob%20Riis%20captured%20New%20York%E2%80%99s%20poorer%20neighbourhoods%20in%20his%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Children%20of%20the%20Poor%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1892)%20as%20a%20mode%20of%20raising%20awareness%20of%20the%20social%20state%20of%20the%20expanding%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fen%2Fexhibits%2Fexhibit%2Fchildren-beyond-armed-conflict%5C%22%3EUnited%20Nations%20employed%20such%20photographs%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20its%20own%20ends.%20UNICEF%20began%20by%20capturing%20child%20victims%20of%20poverty%20in%20the%20late%2019th%20century%2C%20and%20employed%20the%20pictures%20to%20solicit%20sympathy%20and%20contributions%20but%20also%20ramp%20up%20a%20humanitarian%20morality%20around%20the%20figure%20of%20the%20child%20and%20uneven%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F27895958%5C%22%3EPaula%20S.%20Fass%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20noted%20in%20her%20essay%2C%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20Children%E2%80%99s%20Rights%20Convention%20adopted%20in%201959%20made%20use%20of%20such%20pictures%20to%20underline%20its%20point.%20Collections%20such%20as%20UNICEF%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.unhcr.org%2Fen%2Fdocuments%2Fdetails%2F40082%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EUnder%20Siege%3A%20The%20Devastating%20Impacts%20on%20Children%20of%20Three%20Years%20of%20Conflict%20in%20Syria%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2015)%20were%20put%20out%20for%20later%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20longer%20recognisable%20as%20persons%2C%20given%20their%20ruined%20state%2C%20the%20children%20look%20out%20from%20the%20UNICEF%20photographs%2C%20or%20do%20not%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Kurdi%20and%20Kafarneh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EYazan%20Al-Kafarneh%2C%2013%2C%20died%20of%20malnutrition%20today.%20He%20was%20killed%20by%20Israel%20through%20starvation.%20Many%20more%20children%20are%20dead%20or%20dying.%20What%20more%20horrors%20need%20to%20occur%20before%20putting%20an%20end%20to%20this%20genocide%3F!!%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FkhpCGDAQe2%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FkhpCGDAQe2%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Ambassador%20Majed%20Bamya%20%F0%9F%87%B5%F0%9F%87%B8%20(%40majedbamya)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmajedbamya%2Fstatus%2F1764646518265430118%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%204%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20extreme%20vulnerability%20of%20Kurdi%20and%20Kafarneh%2C%20beyond%20their%20fragile%20bodies%2C%20the%20photographs%20achieve%20something%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20children%20traditionally%20associated%20with%20not%20just%20innocence%20but%20embodying%20potential%20are%20captured%20embedded%20in%20a%20context%20in%20which%20no%20future%20can%20possibly%20unfold.%20Starvation%2C%20absence%20of%20healthcare%20and%20unrelenting%20conflict%20are%20the%20contexts%20in%20which%20a%20Kafarneh-with-potential%20becomes%20a%20victim%2C%20one%20whose%20potential%20has%20been%20erased%20fully.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhich%20means%20to%20say%2C%20the%20sites%2C%20whether%20bombed%20ruins%20or%20hospital%20beds%2C%20are%20sites%20where%20no%20future%20abides.%20If%20potential%20and%20capability%20require%20a%20sustaining%20environment%20in%20which%20to%20reach%20fruition%2C%20then%20the%20context%20in%20which%20Kurdi%20or%20Kafarneh%20are%20embedded%20ensures%20that%20no%20potential%20is%20ever%20likely%20to%20be%20fulfilled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20photographs%20then%20are%20not%20of%20the%20children%20alone%3A%20they%20point%20to%20the%20material%20conditions%20in%20which%20a%20certain%20kind%20of%20future%20alone%20rests.%20The%20pictures%20are%20not%20about%20the%20present%3A%20they%20are%20about%20a%20%3Cem%3Efuture%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20which%2C%20possibly%2C%20there%20will%20be%20no%20children%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20the%20scenes%20of%20destruction%20that%20we%20see%20unfolding%20on%20our%20screens%20today%2C%20whether%20of%20barren%20lands%20or%20devastated%20lands%2C%20force%20us%20to%20shift%20from%20ruin%20to%20rubble.%20The%20ruin%2C%20which%20has%20its%20own%20melancholic%20appeal%20and%20sense%20of%20mystery%2C%20is%20now%20just%20plain%20rubble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20child%20victim%20does%20not%20connect%20to%20the%20ruin%3A%20s%2Fhe%20is%20%3Cem%3Eof%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20rubble%2C%20a%20part%20of%20it%2C%20broken%2C%20dismembered%20and%20poignantly%20separated%20from%20a%20context%20in%20which%20s%2Fhe%20would%20have%20otherwise%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20landscape%20of%20conflict%20where%20Kafarneh%20is%20to%20be%20%E2%80%98found%E2%80%99%20(a%20wholly%20inappropriate%20word%2C%20given%20that%20he%20starved%20to%20death%20in%20his%20%E2%80%98home%E2%80%99)%20is%20a%20place%20where%20matter%20has%20lost%20its%20form.%20The%20hospital%2C%20the%20home%20and%20the%20school%20are%20no%20longer%20the%20same%3A%20their%20form%20has%20been%20broken%20down%20into%20bricks%2C%20mortar%20and%20steel%20due%20to%20the%20bombings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F4D0Xc6ppHro%3Fsi%3DSpUupQaVY5JUWrjj%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaterial%20matter%2C%20which%20had%20been%20formed%20into%20structures%20for%20a%20Kafarneh%20to%20live%20in%2C%20play%20in%20and%20study%20in%2C%20has%20returned%20to%20a%20pre-form%2C%20by%20which%20I%20mean%20a%20state%20%3Cem%3Eprior%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20all%20form%20state%3A%20rubble.%20The%20ruins%20of%20buildings%20may%20still%20be%20functional%2C%20at%20least%20minimally.%20But%20their%20intended%20service%20and%20purpose%20are%20altered%20once%20the%20ruination%20has%20set%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20this%20loss%20of%20form%20and%20function%20%E2%80%93%20of%20the%20hospital%2C%20the%20home%2C%20the%20school%20%E2%80%93%20that%20produces%20the%20child%20victim.%20Kafarneh%20died%20in%20a%20hospital%20bed%2C%20but%20he%20arrives%20via%20a%20landscape%20smashed%20to%20smithereens%20and%20in%20a%20state%20of%20advanced%20starvation%2C%20according%20to%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hospital%20is%20of%20no%20functional%20use%20because%20life%20among%20the%20rubble%20has%20made%20it%20impossible%20that%20the%20new%20matter%20(the%20form%20and%20function%20of%20the%20hospital)%20can%20revive%20that%20life.%20Just%20as%20the%20hospital%2C%20home%20and%20school%20are%20rendered%20into%20waste%2C%20so%20is%20the%20child%E2%80%99s%20body%20that%20occupies%20those%20spaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20a%20tragic%20correlation%20between%20the%20wasting%20%E2%80%93%20intended%2C%20of%20course%2C%20through%20bombings%20%E2%80%93%20building%20and%20the%20wasted%20child.%20In%20these%20spaces%2C%20the%20human%20form%2C%20particularly%20of%20the%20child%2C%20is%20inverted%20into%20mere%20flesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruined%20body%20of%20Kafarneh%2C%20within%20the%20precincts%20of%20the%20hospital%20where%20he%20died%2C%20does%20not%20point%20to%20the%20hospital.%20It%20points%20to%20the%20landscape%20he%20came%20%3Cem%3Ethrough%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20ruined%20or%20damaged%20hospital%20is%20newness%20because%20the%20original%20hospital%20is%20only%20in%20the%20past.%20Likewise%20is%20Kafarneh%20lying%20in%20bed%2C%20emaciated%20to%20a%20point%20where%20there%20is%20little%20matter%20(flesh)%20on%20him%20(and%20the%20eyes%20seem%20overly%20large%20as%20a%20result).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conflict%20and%20the%20bombing%20therefore%20produce%20new%20matter%3A%20the%20ruined%20hospital%20of%20the%20present%20and%20the%20starving%20body%20in%20the%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETraditionally%2C%20the%20dissolving%20human%20body%20%E2%80%93%20the%20liquefaction%20%E2%80%93%20is%20the%20stuff%20of%20nightmares%20and%20much%20Gothic%20and%20neo-Gothic%20horror.%20But%20neither%20Kurdi%20nor%20Kafarneh%20are%20dissolved%20bodies.%20The%20horror%20we%20see%20is%20the%20%3Cem%3Ecorpus%20intacta%3C%2Fem%3E%20but%20diminished.%20It%20invokes%20greater%20horror%2C%20one%20could%20argue%2C%20not%20because%20it%20is%20broken%20but%20because%20it%20is%20whole%20and%20yet%20not-alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-worlds-indifference-to-palestinian-genocide-will-cost-more-lives%5C%22%3EThe%20World%E2%80%99s%20Indifference%20to%20Palestinian%20Genocide%20Will%20Cost%20More%20Lives%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWriting%20about%20the%20Abu%20Ghraib%20visuals%2C%20the%20critic%20Susan%20Sontag%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20live%20is%20to%20be%20photographed%2C%20to%20have%20a%20record%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20life%2C%20and%20therefore%20to%20go%20on%20with%20one%E2%80%99s%20life%20oblivious%2C%20or%20claiming%20to%20be%20oblivious%2C%20to%20the%20camera%E2%80%99s%20nonstop%20attentions.%20But%20to%20live%20is%20also%20to%20pose.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20sense%2C%20Kurdi%20and%20Kafarneh%20are%20posed%3A%20captured%20on%20camera%20in%20a%20particular%20state.%20Except%20that%20this%20state%20is%20not%20a%20pose%20emanating%20from%20life.%20It%20is%20a%20record%2C%20to%20adapt%20Sontag%E2%80%99s%20words%2C%20of%20how%20a%20life%20%3Cem%3Ecould%20not%20be%20lived%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Eany%20more%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20photograph%20captures%20a%20body%20transitioned%20from%20the%20living%20to%20the%20non-living%3A%20just%20inert%20matter%20on%20a%20beach%20(Kurdi)%20or%20a%20bed%20(Kafarneh).%20The%20human%20descends%2C%20reversing%20the%20normative%20of%20life%20lived%20towards%20a%20future%2C%20into%20the%20abhuman%20(starvation%2C%20in%20this%20most%20recent%20case)%20and%20eventually%20the%20non-living.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%209%2F11%20novel%2C%20%3Cem%3EFalling%20Man%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Don%20DeLillo%20writes%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20something%20that%20belonged%20to%20another%20landscape%2C%20something%20inserted%2C%20a%20conjuring%20that%20resembled%20for%20the%20briefest%20second%20some%20half-seen%20image%20only%20half%20believed%20in%20the%20seeing%2C%20when%20the%20witness%20wonders%20what%20has%20happened%20to%20the%20meaning%20of%20things%2C%20to%20tree%2C%20stone%2C%20wind%2C%20simple%20words%20lost%20in%20the%20falling%20ash.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20it%20is%20another%20landscape%3A%20a%20once-pulsing%2C%20thriving%20land%20is%20transformed%20into%20unrecognisable%20forms%20of%20rubble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20essay%20titled%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fbooks%2F2001%2Fdec%2F22%2Ffiction.dondelillo%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20Ruins%20of%20the%20Future%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20this%20same%20Don%20DeLillo%20wrote%3A%20%E2%80%9CFor%20all%20those%20who%20may%20want%20what%20we%E2%80%99ve%20got%2C%20there%20are%20all%20those%20who%20do%20not.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%20did%20want%20the%20same%20thing%20for%20Kurdi%20and%20Kafarneh%3A%20life.%20So%20we%20%3Cem%3Eknow%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20meaning%20of%20things%20buried%20beneath%20the%20ash%20of%20this%20smoking%20rubble%3A%20a%20future%20ended%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20there%20will%20be%20none.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fpramod-k-nayar%5C%22%3EPramod%20K.%20Nayar%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0teaches%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Hyderabad.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710066801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F16094246%2Fimage1440x560cropped.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fand-then-there-were-none-yazan-kafarneh%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Traditionally%2C%20the%20dissolving%20human%20body%20is%20the%20stuff%20of%20nightmares.%20But%20Yazan%20Kafarneh%20is%20not%20a%20dissolved%20body.%20The%20horror%20we%20see%20is%20the%20corpus%20intacta%20but%20diminished.%20It%20invokes%20greater%20horror%20not%20because%20it%20is%20broken%20but%20because%20it%20is%20whole%20and%20yet%20not-alive.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fand-then-there-were-none-yazan-kafarneh%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22ChatGPT%20uses%2017k%20times%20more%20electricity%20than%20US%20household%20in%20a%20day%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710066266000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108368117%2Cimgsize-1769792.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fgadgets-news%2Falarming-ai-numbers-chatgpt-uses-17000-times-more-electricity-than-an