with-disability-low-earners-gig-work-flexibility-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20with%20disabilities%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20to%20drive%20around%20chemotherapy%20appointments%20or%20school%20drop-offs.%20However%2C%20Cameron%20added%20that%20drivers%20who%20are%20more%20financially%20dependent%20on%20these%20apps%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20accept%20lower%20fare%20amounts%20as%20they%20need%20the%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20drivers%20are%20lured%20into%20gig%20work%20by%20promises%20of%20flexibility%2C%20though%20Avedian%20said%20growing%20competition%20has%20made%20it%20so%20that%20more%20profitable%20rides%20are%20harder%20to%20secure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFlexibility%20and%20freedom%20was%20a%20massive%20selling%20point%20because%20the%20demand%20was%20outstripping%20supply%2C%20but%20for%20the%20last%20three%2C%20four%20years%2C%20that's%20kind%20of%20out%20of%20the%20window%2C%26quot%3B%20Avedian%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20for%20that%20is%20every%20single%20market%20that%20I%20know%20of%20is%20extremely%20oversaturated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorking%20on%20their%20own%20terms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20many%20drivers%20would%20rather%20work%20on%20their%20own%20terms%20than%20have%20a%20set%20work%20schedule.%20Laura%20Katsnelson%2C%20a%20doctoral%20candidate%20in%20the%20Strategy%20Unit%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20gig%20drivers%20%26quot%3Bderive%20substantial%20value%20from%20being%20able%20to%20change%20which%20hours%20they%20work%20from%20week%20to%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20though%20demand%20conditions%20likely%20impact%20when%20drivers%20choose%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20paper%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hbs.edu%2Ffaculty%2FPages%2Fitem.aspx%3Fnum%3D60255%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBeing%20the%20Boss%3A%20Gig%20Workers'%20Value%20of%20Flexible%20Work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20and%20her%20colleague%20Felix%20Oberholzer-Gee%20found%20that%20when%20the%20average%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-uber-eats-lyft-doordash-instacart-grubhub-drivers-make-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDoorDash%3C%2Fa%3E%20driver%20is%20forced%20to%20work%20exclusively%20in%20their%20most%20frequently%20driven%20blocks%20of%20time%2C%20hourly%20earnings%20are%20cut%20by%20over%2011%25.%20Given%20this%20arrangement%2C%20over%20two-thirds%20would%20be%20projected%20to%20drop%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20assume%20that%20if%20they%20chose%20a%20particular%20time%20to%20work%20on%20the%20platform%2C%20it's%20because%20it%20made%20the%20most%20sense%20for%20them%20given%20their%20set%20of%20circumstances%20at%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EKatsnelson%20said.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20it%20may%20very%20well%20be%20that%20certain%20drivers%20would%20prefer%20a%20world%20in%20which%20they%20could%20work%20a%209-5%20job%20with%20employee%20benefits%20that%20pays%20'enough'%20for%20them%20to%20get%20by.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20there%20are%20likely%20other%20subsets%20of%20drivers%20who%20are%20well-served%20by%20the%20current%20DoorDash%20model%20because%20they%20use%20it%20to%20flexibly%20supplement%20their%20income.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EChasing%20more%20lucrative%20rides%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKatie%20Wells%2C%20a%20geographer%20at%20Georgetown%20University%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BDisrupting%20DC%3A%20The%20Rise%20of%20Uber%20and%20the%20Fall%20of%20the%20City%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20that%20in%20her%20research%2C%20many%20drivers%20said%20they%20would%20arrange%20their%20schedules%20around%20the%20hopes%20of%20encountering%20incentives%20offered%20by%20platforms%20like%20bonuses%2C%20sometimes%20working%20split%20shifts.%20This%20helps%20them%20maximize%20their%20earnings%2C%20but%20many%20feel%20like%20it's%20their%20only%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20drivers%20told%20her%20they%20would%20work%2016-hour%20overnight%20shifts%20on%20weekends%20to%20find%20higher-paying%2C%20better-tipped%20rides.%20She%20said%20one%20driver%20worked%20from%207%20a.m.%20to%2010%20a.m.%2C%20then%20from%204%20p.m.%20to%2010%20p.m.%2C%20because%20he%20could%20only%20make%20a%20profit%20during%20these%20periods.%20He%20was%20%26quot%3Bfree%26quot%3B%20to%20choose%20his%20schedule%2C%20Wells%20said%2C%20but%20driving%20whenever%20he%20pleased%20would%20mean%20fewer%20profitable%20rides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20flexibility%20of%20the%20gig%20economy%20is%20a%20mirage%2C%20and%20quite%20a%20costly%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20Wells%20said.%20%26quot%3BUber%20and%20its%20peers%20appeal%20to%20workers%20with%20oodles%20of%20promises%20that%20workers%20can%20hold%20the%20power%20to%20control%20their%20work%20hours.%20However%2C%20the%20reality%20for%20too%20many%20workers%20in%20too%20many%20cities%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20is%20far%20from%20that%20ideal.%20Many%20gig%20workers%20end%20up%20working%20much%20longer%20hours%20than%20they%20hope%2C%20trying%20to%20eke%20out%20decent%20earnings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Avedian%2C%20who%20also%20drives%20part-time%2C%20driving%20during%20peak%20hours%20often%20doesn't%20equate%20to%20higher%20earnings.%20Avedian%20estimated%20his%20utilization%20rate%20is%2050%25%2C%20meaning%20for%20every%20hour%20online%2C%20he%20only%20gives%20rides%20for%20half%20an%20hour.%20He%20estimates%20that%20for%20a%20Saturday%20driving%20from%2010%20a.m.%20to%206%20p.m.%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20his%20gross%20earnings%20are%20%2421%20an%20hour%20before%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20work%20between%2010%20a.m.%20and%202%20p.m.%2C%20there's%20no%20flexibility%20because%20everybody's%20already%20at%20school%2C%20at%20work.%20There%20are%20no%20trips%20out%20there%2C%20and%20you're%20just%20going%20to%20sit%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Avedian%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20order%20for%20you%20to%20maximize%20your%20earnings%2C%20you%20have%